Lagos- Rt. Hon. Mudashiru Obasa, Speaker of the Lagos State House Of Assembly, has sacked his Chief of Staff (CoS), Hon. Saka Fafunmi and Chief Press Secretary (CPS), Mr. Tolani Abati. Obasa also fired his Special Adviser on Political Matters, Hon. Dayo Famakinwa, Special Adviser on Researc and one other Special Adviser. While Fafunmi was a former three term member of the House, Famakinwa also served as a member between 2015and 2019 representing Ajeromi-Ifelodun Constituency. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCEÂ DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! As at the time of filing this report there had been no official communication from the office of the Speaker concerning the reason for their sack. One of the affacted aides who confided in our correspondent, however, explained that their sacked letters were delivered to them in the early hours of Tuesday in which the Speaker thanked them for adding values to his office during their appointments.